A constitution with the breakbar in Egypt
It is a new poker game by President Mohammed Mursi.
While Egypt remains divided more than ever with regard to the constitutional declaration, which temporarily gives him the unlimited power of authority, he has decided to put everything on a map.
As a surprise to all, he announced on Wednesday that the constitutional assembly would adopt its final version the next day.
Just a week ago, the head of state granted this House two additional months to complete its work.
For almost two years now, Egypt has been based on a provisional text, which has been amended several times, which weakens institutional stability and leads to legal confusion.
This new initiative has only led to an even greater division of the country.
For his opponents, the President persists in his "autocratic delirium," by continuing to "break his word" and "to" kick the law with his feet. "
On the basis of its supporters, it is assured that it is a way to end the institutional and political crisis as soon as possible and to speed up the transition process.
A referendum should be held within 14 days.
A very short period, which forces the brothers to renounce their intention to explain the text section by section to the Egyptians.
For the President, it is also a way of restoring his public and democratic legitimacy, while the protest is raging throughout the country.
After affirmation in an interview with the American weekly show Time, Mohammed Mursi seems to be convinced that the Egyptians will vote in favour.
In particular, as an ultimatum is put to the Egyptian people by this use of an overhasty vote: "Either you vote in favour of my draft or I maintain the unlimited power of authority," the latter should probably end after the adoption of the Constitution.
85 most of the Islamist members of this constitutional assembly adopted the text yesterday in a strange atmosphere.
The majority of the Liberals have not complied with the call.
Shortly before the Constitutional Declaration in mid-November, they turned their backs because they believe that they have not been able to make their views known.
Representatives of human rights organisations, religious minorities or civil society have acted equally.
In order to achieve the decision-making capacity, 11 people, deputy members, were added in all haste yesterday morning.
Some are very close to the Muslim brothers.
It is not surprising that the articles were mostly adopted unanimously.
The commentators, by the way, found it entertaining that the only difference of opinion of the day... was expressed in the time for prayer, as some members of the board felt that the pendulum watch of the constitutional assembly was not going well.
The text, which was adopted last night, consists of 234 articles.
Finally, Article 2, which drew all the attention to it, remains the same as that of the 1971 Constitution and states that "the principles of Sharia are the main source of justice."
The Salafist parties, for which the establishment of Islamic law is an important demand, had the hope of replacing "the principles" with "the rules," which would have made it possible to apply more strictly.
For the Islamists, the fact that this article has not been amended is proof of their good will and respect for the other members of Egyptian society.
"hypocrisy" is the response of the liberals, who only consider this as a propaganda attack.
According to them, the Islamization of the Constitution is carried out through other articles.
They are particularly concerned with Article 220, which gives the University of Al-Azhar an advisory role, in particular with regard to the verification of compliance with the laws of the Sharia.
According to Egyptian specialist Sophie Pommier, this is worrying because "the people who are invited to an opinion have not been elected and have no democratic legitimacy.
