Most lawyers who have worked on this text are not Ulema, but academics who have been partly trained in the French system, "says Alexis Brouet, who writes a doctoral thesis on the Egyptian constitutional transition.
He admitted, however, that "there may be ambiguity in Article 220, since the terms used are derived from the religious vocabulary.
