In Israel Ukrainian tourists expect sacred sites, the navel of the world and a sea of Sole
The Promised Land combines in itself the glory of biblical truths, modern comfort and untouched nature.
AIF calls you the five most important reasons for a visit to Israel.
Bend before the holy places
Visit the river Jordan, where Jesus was baptized.
It is said that all who prayed in this river receive God's blessing.
Galilee is the place where Jesus performed his wonders: the transformation of water into wine at a wedding party, the walking on the water, the silence of the sea tower and the fishing of fish.
Right here, Jesus appeared to his disciples after the resurrection.
However, most of the sanctuaries are found in Jerusalem.
Believers here commit the way of suffering or the way of the Cross of Jesus Christ (in Latin: Via Dolorosa).
The path begins at the Roman fortress of Antonia, Pretorium, where the court was, and leads through the streets of the old town to the tomb church on the mountain of Golgotha, where the crucifixion, the anointing stone and the grave of Jesus are located.
Here, according to the Christian view, is the navel of the world, which symbolizes the salvation of humanity.
The monastery of the Holy Cross in Jerusalem is at the place where, according to a Christian legend, the tree from which the cross was made for the crucifixion of Jesus grew.
In Jerusalem is also the most holy place of the Jews - the Klagemauer, the remains of a temple destroyed by the Romans in 70 AD.
As a tradition, people of different beliefs leave notes with wishes, which then go into fulfillment.
Make a trip to the height
