Only mountaineers can reach the ruins from their own power.
All the others bring an airway to this historic summit.
In the north of the country, between 1600 and 2040 meters high, is the famous ski resort Hermon, to which it attracts countless tourists in the winter months.
From the foot of the mountain you can get there with a shuttle bus.
The ski slopes have a total length of 45 km.
According to an old legend, pagan gods lived on the mountain summit.
Visit unique museums
There are almost 300 museums in this country.
With only one trip, not all of them can be visited.
But at least the five most interesting of them should be allowed a visit.
One of these is the Israel Museum not far from the Knesset (Parliament).
There are old Qumran manuscripts or scriptures from the Dead Sea, found in rock caves in the Jewish desert, as well as about 500 thousand archaeological and anthropological exhibits.
The Museum of Art in Tel Aviv is also worth a visit.
The collection of works by the Impressionists and Expressionists Monet, Pissaro, Renoir, Cézanne, Sisley, Matisse, Modigliani, Chagall and Picasso is published there.
In Akko you can visit the Museum in the Bad Al Basha, which houses several rooms of old Turkish baths with sculptures of the then visitors and bathers.
In Caesarea you should visit the unique private Ralli Museum, where you can admire sculptures of Dali and Rodin.
There are no museum guides or souvenir shops.
The admission is free and donations are generally rejected.
The fifth museum, the Holocaust Museum or Yad Vashem in Tel Aviv, tells about one of the most shocking chapters of history.
The most striking department is the monument for the children, which was built to commemorate the 1.5 million children destroyed in the concentration camps and gas chambers.
There is complete darkness in entering the room.
The stars are sparing.
And the names of the Jewish children and the countries in which they died.
Ukraine is also mentioned there.
Do something for health
The three most important recreational areas of Israel are located on the shores of the Mediterranean, the Red Sea and the Dead Sea.
In each of the three places there are swimming pools, water parks, delfinariums and oceanariums.
It is amazing that the Red Sea is also bathing in the winter months, as the water temperature does not fall below 21 ° C and the air is warming up to 23 ° C.
The Dead Sea is even warmer and is bathed all year round.
By the way, this unusual sea with a location of 417 meters below sea level is the deepest sea in the world.
Its turquoise blue water has a high salt content and therefore even does not have a problem on the surface.
The surrounding landscape is indescribably beautiful.
Visitors come here for treatment using saltwater (natural salt sole) and healing sludge as well as for the treatment of skin inflammation, allergies, asthma, eczema, arthritis, bronchitis, diabetes and for the calming of strained nerves.
