From Friday night to the sunset on Saturday, markets and shops are closed, and public transport is resting.
And on Sunday morning, the working week begins.
In many cafés, restaurants and restaurants, only kosher food is served, excluding pork, marine products, fish without shed and food containing both milk and meat products.
Instead, you have the choice between various dishes with ham and beef, soups and desserts (prepared with coconut milk), traditional Jewish humus paste, various sauces, fried balls of purebred beans and peas (falafel) and fruits and vegetables.
