The few information circulating among journalists was received by the press speakers of some of the Unasur governments present at the meeting, but not by the Peruvian press speaker.
The only document that was distributed during the day was the list of participating presidents, which led to displeasure among hundreds of journalists from various national and international media who asked for more information.
The President of Peru then sent the media an e-mail with the "Final Declaration" of the summit, but it was the Humala Declaration and not the official document to conclude the summit.
Last October, Peru hosted the III. South America - Arab States (ASPA) Summit, and also on this occasion, despite a strong press call, the so-called Lima Declaration, which was announced before, was not published.
On the official website of the ASPA you can convince yourself that the document was published last Tuesday.
