The presidents of Peru, Ollanta Humala, and Chile, Sebastián Piñera, met during the regional meeting and confirmed that they would accept the decision of the IGH, which starts on Monday in The Hague, in the process that Lima initiated against Santiago, to listen to the pleas of both sides.
"We will follow and implement the judgment on the differences we are currently presenting to this international court," said Humala, together with his Chilean counterpart.
