Larry Hagman, whose role as the oil magnate J.R. Ewing in the television series "Dallas" has become a symbol of the greed of the 1980s, is dead.
He was 81 years old.
Hagman, who came back this year as J.R. in a new season of "Dallas," died on Friday afternoon due to cancer complications according to a family press release to The Associated Press by Warner Bros., producer of "Dallas."
"Larry was back in his beloved town of Dallas, where he once again played the iconic role that he liked most," said the family.
Larry's family and his closest friends were with him in Dallas for the celebration of the harvest thanks.
